	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Octo 22 1850</date></p>
				<p>Dear Doctor</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. Newman</persName> one of the<lb/> most learned Professors of the Hebrew<lb/> language we have had in the Country is<lb/> on a visit to the <placeName>United States</placeName> to see<lb/> if there is any opening for him either as<lb/> teacher or lecturer. He has instructed<lb/> some of the most <sic>preminet</sic><add>&#63;</add> men in<lb/> <placeName>England</placeName> and with his learning  &#38; good character<lb/> would have <sic>ammended</sic> any Chair<lb/> had he been willing to have <sic>surrenderd</sic> his<lb/> faith In this country it will be no obstacle<lb/> to him and should there be any vacancy<lb/> in the <placeName>Maryland</placeName> Colleges or as a lecturer<lb/> any where to which you can recommend<lb/> him I am quite certain that you will<lb/> have no cause to regret it. He is a<lb/> plain simple man in his habits &#38; manners<lb/> but one worthy of being cherished</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">always Dear Doctor</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">very truly yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M M Noah</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>D. Joshua Cohen</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Indy<add>&#63;</add>. <persName role="author">Noah</persName>. MR<add>&#63;</add></p>
				<p><date>Oct. 28 50</date>.</p>
		</body>
